Bean Scopes:

1.Singleton
2.Prototype
3.Request
4.Session


1.Singleton:
-Single bean created at the time of application startup and share accross the entire spring container.
-It is eager loading - because it create bean immediately while application start

------------------------**------------------------

@Component
public class Employee {

	public Employee() {
		System.out.println("Employee Bean Created");
	}

}


@RestController
public class Controller {

  public Controller() {
		System.out.println("Controller Bean Created");
	}

	@Autowired
	Employee employee1;

	@Autowired
	Employee employee2;

	@Autowired
	Employee employee3;

	@GetMapping("/getStudent1")
	public int getEmployee1() {
		return employee1.hashCode();
	}

	@GetMapping("/getStudent2")
	public int getEmployee2() {
		return employee2.hashCode();
	}

	@GetMapping("/getStudent3")
	public int getEmployee3() {
		return employee3.hashCode();
	}

}

//output: only one bean created and every API return same hashcode due to single bean
Console Print while application run:
Controller Bean Created
Employee Bean Created

------------------------**------------------------


2.Prototype:
A new instance is created each time the bean is requested.
-It is lazy loading - because it create bean only when request

------------------------**------------------------

